<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF2B6A94FCE894581A70BF2C" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF2B6A94FCE894581A70BF2C" blockId="208.[786,1380,430,857]" lastBlockId="208.[170,1380,864,3068]" pageId="208" pageNumber="970">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FC5694581DFEB92C" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[938,1022,513,542]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FBEE94581A8CB92C" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1042,1164,513,542]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">horsfieldii</taxonomicName>
species group. See 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FCB294711DC7B977" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1898" box="[846,967,552,581]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ridleyi">M. ridleyi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FBF794711AA7B977" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1035,1191,552,581]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adversus">M. adversus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FB4A94711D42B95F" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">Myotis macropus</taxonomicName>
appears to be relative to M. hasselti, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FCE9942E1DDDB9A6" baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[789,989,631,660]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrotarsus">M. macrotarsus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FC13942E1A9BB9A6" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1007,1179,631,660]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="969" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="horsfieldii">M. horsfieldii</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FB12942E1D46B98E" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
based on limited genetic data. Specimens throughout northern and 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF2B6A94FB0A949B1D8FB838" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="208" pageNumber="970">western Australia</collectingRegion>
that were previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FCE895491DB1B803" baseAuthorityName="Horsfield" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[788,945,784,817]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adversus">M. adversus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FC0495491AC3B803" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1915" box="[1016,1219,784,817]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moluccarum">M. moluccarum</taxonomicName>
now represent 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FCA495611A01B86B" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[856,1025,824,857]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">M. macropus</taxonomicName>
. There appear to be two genetic clades in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF2B6A94FE5D95391C20B8B3" box="[417,544,864,897]" name="Australia" pageId="208" pageNumber="970">Australia</collectingCountry>
, one in the north and north-east and the other in the west and south-west that likely correspond to subspecies (possibly 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FBE195DE1A94B89A" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1053,1172,903,936]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">macropus</taxonomicName>
and richards). 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FF5295F61F7BB8E2" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[174,379,943,976]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">Myotis australis</taxonomicName>
, known only from the holotype in 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF2B6A94FC8195F61A78B8E2" box="[893,1144,943,976]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="208" pageNumber="970">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
, is considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FEAB958F1FFEB8C5" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[343,510,982,1015]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macropus">M. macropus</taxonomicName>
because no other species of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FC6D958F1DE5B8C5" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[913,997,982,1015]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
has been confirmed there; it could still represent a vagrant of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FD6495A41CF7BF2C" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[664,759,1021,1054]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="959" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2B6A94FCD995A41DC3BF2C" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[805,963,1021,1054]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF2B6A94FF5192701DF5BFA7" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF2B6A94FF5192701DF5BFA7" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398962" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398962/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="208" pageNumber="970" targetBox="[171,764,442,857]" targetPageId="208">
